  "prompt": "How long does it take to open a savings bank account in ICICI bank?",
  "response": "The time it takes to open a savings account with ICICI Bank can vary based on the method you choose and the completeness of your documentation. Here\u2019s a general breakdown:\n\n### 1. **In-Branch Application**  \n   If you visit an ICICI Bank branch with all the required documents (e.g., ID proof, address proof, PAN card, photographs, etc.), the process typically takes **30 minutes to 1 hour** for verification and account activation. However, in some cases, it may take up to **24-48 hours** for the account to be fully operational.\n\n### 2. **Online Application**  \n   If you apply online through ICICI Bank's website or mobile app, the process is quicker. You can complete the application in **10-15 minutes**, provided you have all the necessary documents ready for upload. Once your documents are verified (which usually takes **1-2 business days**), your account will be activated.\n\n### 3. **Instant Account Opening**  \n   ICICI Bank offers some instant account opening options (e.g., through their mobile app). If you meet the eligibility criteria and provide valid KYC documents, your account can be opened **instantly**, and you\u2019ll receive the account details immediately.\n\n### Factors Affecting the Timeline:\n- **Documentation:** Incomplete or incorrect documents can delay the process.\n- **Verification:** If video KYC or physical verification is required, it may take additional time.\n- **Banking Hours:** Applications submitted outside banking hours or on weekends may take longer to process.\n\n### Tips for Faster Processing:\n- Ensure all documents are valid and up-to-date.\n- Double-check the information provided in the application.\n- Opt for video KYC if available, as it speeds up the process.\n\nIn summary, the process can range from **instant activation** (online/instant account opening) to **1-2 business days** (in-branch or online with verification delays).",
  "temperature": 1.0,
